Five books about the work of the great German writer Thomas Mann in pdf format. These are books for beginners and students, not advanced scholars.



The Cambridge Companion to Thomas Mann (edited by Ritchie Robertson)

A Companion to the Works of Thomas Mann (edited by Herbert Lehnert and Eva Wessell)

Thomas Mann (from the series: Bloom's Major Short Story Writers, edited by Harold Bloom)

Understanding Thomas Mann (by Hannelore Mundt)

Mann: Buddenbrooks (by Hugh Ridley, from the series: Landmarks of World Literature)

